##Scale the data

from scipy.stats import zscore

df_z = df.apply(zscore)
In [33]:
#Finding optimal no. of clusters
from scipy.spatial.distance import cdist
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

clusters=range(1,10)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(df_z)
    prediction=model.predict(df_z)
    meanDistortions.append(sum(np.min(cdist(df_z, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / df_z.shape[0])


plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method')
Out[33]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Selecting k with the Elbow Method')

Though the bend is not coming out clearly as there are many bends, let us look at 3 clusters and 4 clusters

Hierarchial vs K-Means Clustering comparison¶

  1. We have almost similar silhouette score for both Kmeans and agglomerative clusters of size 3

  2. we have the best result for the agglomerative Hierarchial clustering using the average linkage method as the cophenet index seems to be the highest amongest all the other linkage methods

  3. Shape of Clusters are almost similar. this may be due to smaller dataset. we may observe difference in cluster shape if our dataset is bigger

  1. How many different segments of customers are there?

    Customers can be broadly segmented into 3 Customer segments.

    1. Based on Avg Credit Card Limit,
    2. Based on number of credit cards
    3. Based on their interaction with customer services.

  1. How are these segments different from each other?

    These segments are different from each other based on their credit limit, number of credit cards owned and how they interact with the banks customer services.

  1. What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?
    1. The recommendations to the bank is to have different strategies to retain and increase customer value by target low value customers (less than 3 credit card) with marketing strategies to increase their credit limits and offer incentives to acquire more credit cards. Also since these customers are primarily interacting with the bank over calls to the customer service center, an improved customer experience on the calls will help retain them and increase value.
    2. For customers who are in the mid range value (Less than 6 credit cards) who prefer to visit the bank and interact directly with the bank, to focus marketing strategy to up-sell more when they visit the bank and also provide better experience at the bank location
    3. for customers who are high value (greater than 6 credit cards) who prefer to interact using online method, the bank can focus on improving their experience online and upsell other services and ensure that these customers are retained and remain as customer
